Why Is My Free Hostname in Redemption?

Free hostnames remain active for 30 days. If you do not confirm your hostname within 30 days the hostname will expire and be removed from DNS. Not confirming the hostname during the confirmation period or during the grace period when it was removed from DNS will place the hostname in redemption.

Why Does No-IP Have a Redemption Period?

This process helps protect you by providing a final period of retrieval before the hostname can be created by anyone. Hostnames in redemption are essentially “locked” and reserved for you.
